- RAG reduces hallucination from 15-30% to under 5% but adds latency proportional to corpus size
- Knowledge graphs enable multi-hop reasoning that flat retrieval cannot support
- Synthesis engine pairs nodes by cosine similarity (0.5 floor, 0.92 ceiling) for cross-pollination
- Node salience decays 2% every 10 cycles; breakthroughs are exempt via weight floor
- Partition boundaries prevent cross-domain pairing unless explicitly bridged